value.def: A bushel is a unit of volume that is used for measuring agricultural produce such as corn or beans. A bushel is equivalent in volume to eight gallons.

defx.def: If you hide your light under a bushel, you keep your abilities or good qualities hidden from other people.
defx.tran: 不露锋芒；（才华）藏而不露
